    <div class="article-intro"><div class="article-hero"><img src="/assets/screens/en-point-720.webp" width="1280" height="720" alt="VeVolt charging location with tariff information" fetchpriority="high"></div><header class="article-header"><p class="eyebrow"><span class="signal"></span>VeVolt guide</p><h1>Free or paid EV charging station: how to know before arriving</h1><p class="lede">A charger marked as free may still sit inside paid parking, while a paid charger can include different session or idle fees. Look at the complete stop cost.</p><p class="article-meta">Updated 18/07/2026 · 7 min read</p></header></div>
    <div class="article-layout"><div class="article-body"><section><h2>Read the tariff carefully</h2><p>Check whether billing is per kWh, minute, session or membership. Also look for idle fees that begin after charging ends.</p></section><section><h2>Confirm access conditions</h2><p>Shopping centers, hotels and workplaces may limit charging to customers or guests. Parking and opening hours can matter as much as the energy tariff.</p><ul><li>Energy tariff</li><li>Session fee</li><li>Idle fee</li><li>Parking cost</li><li>Customer or guest requirement</li></ul></section><section><h2>Record what was actually paid</h2><p>After charging, record energy and total amount. Real records make future comparisons more accurate and can help other drivers when shared responsibly.</p></section><section><h2>Frequently asked questions</h2><div class="faq-list"><details class="faq-item"><summary>Does free charging mean free parking?</summary><p>No. Energy and parking are separate charges and must be checked independently.</p></details><details class="faq-item"><summary>Are community prices guaranteed?</summary><p>No. They are contextual reports and may change; confirm at the operator or location.</p></details></div></section></div>
    <aside class="article-aside"><h2>Use VeVolt in your routine</h2><p>Find chargers, check reports, plan alternatives and record your experience in one app.</p><a class="button primary" href="/en/testers">Join the test</a><h2>Sources and further reading</h2><ul class="source-list"><li><a href="https://www.gov.br/aneel/pt-br/assuntos/veiculos-eletricos" rel="noopener noreferrer">ANEEL - Electric vehicles and charging rules</a></li></ul></aside></div>
    <section class="section compact"><div class="section-heading"><div><p class="kicker">Related guides</p><h2>Keep learning</h2></div></div><div class="grid two"><article class="article-card"><div class="article-card-body"><h3>How to check whether an EV charger is working</h3><p>Reduce uncertainty by checking operator status, recent driver reports, access conditions and nearby alternatives.</p><a class="text-link" href="/en/blog/how-to-check-if-an-ev-charger-is-working">Read article →</a></div></article><article class="article-card"><div class="article-card-body"><h3>EV charging-station map in Brazil: how to read the network in 2026</h3><p>Understand public and semi-public charging coverage, connector data, regional gaps and what a map marker really means.</p><a class="text-link" href="/en/blog/ev-charging-station-map-brazil-2026">Read article →</a></div></article></div></section>
